          "ruleId": "CORVUS-MCP10",
          "level": "error",
          "message": {
            "text": "Response Flooding \u2014 'list_items' returns oversized response. Tool 'list_items' returned 18,763 bytes (threshold: 8,192 bytes). Large responses can overflow LLM context windows, push out system prompts, or cause denial-of-service in agent pipelines."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "logicalLocations": [
                {
                  "name": "list_items",
                  "kind": "function"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CORVUS-MCP10",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Response Flooding \u2014 'list_items' returns highly repetitive content. Tool 'list_items' response contains a phrase repeated \u226515 times. Repetitive content can be used to anchor specific instructions into LLM memory or exhaust context budget with low-information noise."
          },
          "locations": [
            {
              "logicalLocations": [
                {
                  "name": "list_items",
                  "kind": "function"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CORVUS-MCP07",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "initialize accepts protocol version downgrade. The server accepted initialize with arbitrary protocol versions: ['9999-99-99', '2030-01-01', '1.0', '2024-01-01', '\"\"', '0.1']. The server also accepted far-future versions, indicating no version validation at all. Servers should reject versions outside their supported range to prevent feature-downgrade attacks."
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CORVUS-MCP07",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "initialize crash \u2014 missing protocolVersion causes unhandled error. Sending initialize without the required protocolVersion field caused the server to crash or return an unexpected result. Servers must validate required fields and return -32602 (Invalid params)."
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CORVUS-MCP07",
          "level": "note",
          "message": {
            "text": "initialize accepts type-confused protocolVersion (integer instead of string). The server accepted an initialize request where protocolVersion was an integer (42) instead of a string. Strict type checking prevents parser confusion and unexpected coercion behavior."
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CORVUS-EXT01",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Null request ID accepted \u2014 JSON-RPC spec violation. The server accepted a request with id=null and returned a result. Per JSON-RPC 2.0, null IDs are reserved for notifications (no response expected). Accepting them may cause response routing bugs in complex orchestration scenarios."
          }
        },
        {
          "ruleId": "CORVUS-EXT01",
          "level": "warning",
          "message": {
            "text": "Server accepts array request ID \u2014 JSON-RPC spec violation. The server returned a successful result to a request with an array as the request ID. JSON-RPC 2.0 requires the id to be a string, number, or null."
          }
        }
      ],
